A N A C T
RELATING TO PUBLIC PROPERTY AND WORKS -- STATE PURCHASES
Introduced By: Representatives Baginski, Lima, Spears, and Solomon
Date Introduced: February 12, 2025
Referred To: House Innovation, Internet, & Technology
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 37-2 of the General Laws entitled "State Purchases" is hereby
2 amended by adding thereto the following section:
3 37-2-83. Prohibiting state agencies from entering into contracts limiting ability to
4 install or run certain software.
5 (a) As used in this section:
6 (1) "State agencies" has the same meaning as defined in ยง 37-2-7.
7 (2) "State software application purchases" means all types of agreements, including grants
8 and orders, for the purchase or disposal of supplies, services, construction, or any other item,
9 entered into by a state agency the cost or price of which is to be paid, in whole or in part, with or
10 out of state funds. It includes awards; contracts of a fixed-price, cost, cost-plus-a-fixed-fee, or
11 incentive type; contracts providing for the issuance of job or task orders; leases; letter contracts;
12 purchase orders; and construction management contracts. It also includes supplemental agreements
13 with respect to any of the foregoing documents.
14 (b) A state contract for the licensing of software applications, which are intended to be
15 installed by a state agency and designed to run on generally available desktop or server hardware,
16 shall not limit a state agency's ability to install or run the software on the hardware of the state
17 agency's choosing.

1 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
